The method and process of preparing foods play important roles in the availability of their nutrients and health benefits, this is one reason why we’re always advised to be mindful of fried foods, the process of frying brings lots of potential harm to the consumer and this is no different when you eat fried plantain.
Plantain is a naturally rich food that looks like a banana, but bigger, it also contains starch and it can be prepared by boiling, roasting, and frying, many people have preferences for different types of plantain according to their method of preparation, for example, I’d go for fried plantain on a good day, and this varies for different people.
Just as plantain has good nutrients and health benefits to back them up, when plantain is fried it becomes dangerous to an extent, this results from the use of oil for Its preparation.
There are different dangers of consuming fried plantain and they include:
√ Increased risk of heart diseases.
√ Increased risk of cancer.
These dangers are enough to scare anyone from eating fried plantain, but it surprises me that many people don’t back down, probably because of the sweet taste of fried plantain, or because of its health benefits.
The key to getting the best out of any food is to eat it moderately no matter how tasty it is, this isn’t different for plantain.
Despite the dangers fried plantain poses you can have your way around it by being moderate in your consumption and changing your preparation method, boiled plantain is not a bad idea and you tend to enjoy the following health benefits when you eat plantain according to WebMD;
1. Reduced risk of constipation
2. Due to the potassium content of plantain it may guard against high blood pressure when consumed moderately.
3. Weight control.
4. Diabetes management.


